OL,3,CFamilies' lives 'will never be the
OL,4,Csame again' after loved ones killed on
OL,5,Croads
OL,7,FMr McCrisken said "The word
OL,8,F'devastating' is used too much
OL,9,Fsometimes these days, but the families
OL,10,Fthat I've dealt with will never be the
OL,11,Fsame again."
OL,13,F"There is the cliche that there is a
OL,14,Fseat less at the table at Christmas -
OL,15,Fthat was the case for at least eight
OL,16,Ffamilies this time last year.
OL,18,F"My message is that if we all make an
OL,19,Feffort, then that might not be the
OL,20,Fcase this year."
